Spec: SpecDD Trace Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in mapping specs to code, tests, docs, changed files, public behavior, references, verification coverage, and gaps.

Owns:
  ./specdd-trace/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-trace/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Inspect implementation, tests, or diffs needed to connect contracts to behavior.
  Identify why each file or spec is included in the trace.
  Preserve the distinction between read context and write authority.
  Identify whether each included item is bootstrap, ancestor spec, nearest local spec, explicit reference, requested file, or changed file.
  Map active constraints or behaviors to code, tests, docs, or tasks that satisfy or fail to satisfy them.
  Report missing links, stale specs, untested scenarios, and unclear authority.

Must not:
  Edit files unless the user explicitly asks for changes.
  Include sibling or nearby specs as authority without an applicable bootstrap rule or explicit reference.
  Expand write authority through referenced or nearby files.
  Treat referenced files as modification scope unless the active spec chain grants it through `Can modify` or `Owns`.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
